../../planning-runs/run-004/attacks/chain-02.md:7:The problem is that the chain is still mostly a Kenig-Merle style template with the key novelty compressed into an undefined phrase: "an exact NS structure unavailable to Tao's averaged model." Until that phrase is made concrete, the chain is not a research program so much as a hope that one missing NS-only rigidity input exists. The biggest risk is not that the chain is too ambitious; it is that it can generate polished memos while never confronting the actual hard obstruction.
../../planning-runs/run-004/attacks/chain-02.md:13:- `L^3` is not just one more critical space on a list. It already sits next to very strong endpoint regularity results, so any minimal-element program there has to explain why those results do not already collapse the route or why the hypothetical critical element evades them only in a very specific way.
../../planning-runs/run-004/attacks/chain-02.md:14:- `\dot H^{1/2}` has a cleaner Hilbert-space profile technology than `BMO^{-1}`, but it is less naturally tied to the suitable-weak-solution machinery that usually feeds local energy and backward-uniqueness style arguments.
../../planning-runs/run-004/attacks/chain-02.md:15:- `BMO^{-1}` is the weakest candidate in this menu for a compactness-rigidity program. It is excellent for small-data mild theory, but it is a poor default host for a large-data minimal blowup extraction unless one can point to a concrete nonlinear profile decomposition and a robust stability theory in exactly that setting.
../../planning-runs/run-004/attacks/chain-02.md:17:So the step's framing is too loose. "Rank realistic spaces" sounds harmless, but the real burden is to prove that at least one space supports the whole package: local theory, perturbation theory, profile decomposition, symmetry normalization, pressure control, and a notion of compactness compatible with the intended rigidity lever. A ranking memo can hide the fact that no candidate actually clears that bar.
../../planning-runs/run-004/attacks/chain-02.md:27:- Requiring Tao-sensitivity before the extraction package is built biases the search toward novelty theater. It rewards mechanisms that sound NS-specific rather than mechanisms that can actually be applied to an almost-periodic critical element.
../../planning-runs/run-004/attacks/chain-02.md:29:There is also a sequencing problem. In most compactness-rigidity programs, the hypothetical critical element tells you what rigidity information is even geometrically available. Here the chain asks for the rigidity weapon before it knows the target's regularity, compactness modulus, or pressure information. That is backwards.
../../planning-runs/run-004/attacks/chain-02.md:37:- Formulating a minimal blowup object in Navier-Stokes is not bookkeeping. It requires a serious extraction package, not just a template borrowed from dispersive PDE.
../../planning-runs/run-004/attacks/chain-02.md:43:The kill condition again sounds precise but is softer than it looks. A "clean formulation" can be written on paper while still relying on unproved profile decomposition, unproved critical stability, or an incompatible solution class. The step should fail unless the object is definable with a clear dependency graph to known results and one sharply identified missing theorem.
