./missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-03.md:94:That template is powerful, but here it may be more a framing trap than a guide. The chain assumes that if local mechanism hunts fail, the right global object is a minimal blowup profile. That is a substantive bet, not a neutral fallback. Navier-Stokes may resist this style of attack precisely because the available rigidity inputs are too weak or too noncritical to close the loop.
