./runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-run-001-attacker-01.log:659:./runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-run-001-planner.log:952:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/vasseur-pressure/library-inbox/exploration-002-interpolation-route-failure.md:194:From De Giorgi energy: ||∇v_k||_{L^2} ≤ U_k^{1/2} but ||∇v_k||_{L^3} requires W^{1,3} of v_k, which requires Morrey-type estimates. These are NOT available from L^{8/3}_t L^4_x regularity of u. [COMPUTED — exponent check in code/sobolev_threshold.py]
./runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-run-001-attacker-01.log:664:./runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-run-001-planner.log:957:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/vasseur-pressure/library-inbox/exploration-002-interpolation-route-failure.md:251:**Note on `sobolev_threshold.py` output:** The "critical exponent table" in that script computes the SPATIAL CZ estimate (u ∈ L^{2q} → p ∈ L^q in R^3). The GOAL's "beta = 4/3" comes from the parabolic mixed-norm estimate on Q_k (u ∈ L^{8/3}_t L^4_x → p ∈ L^{4/3}_t L^2_x → p ∈ L^{4/3}(Q_k) after Hölder). The table's "q=2 gives beta=3" is the pure spatial CZ (u ∈ L^6 → |u|^2 ∈ L^3 → p ∈ L^3 spatially), which is a different norm than the space-time L^{4/3}(Q_k). The W^{1,3} threshold conclusion is unaffected by this distinction. [CONJECTURED — the exact relationship between mixed-norm and space-time exponents in the parabolic De Giorgi setting would require more careful analysis]
