+# `BMO^{-1}` Is Not Admitted Without A Large-Data Replacement Package
+
+Status: `VERIFIED`
+
+For the beyond-De Giorgi Step-1 host-space audit, `BMO^{-1}` should be
+excluded before full package comparison.
+
+Reason:
+
+- the local record supports `BMO^{-1}` only as a strong small-data mild-theory
+  space;
+- the same local record says it is a poor default host for a large-data
+  minimal-blowup extraction;
+- no concrete nonlinear profile decomposition is supplied locally for the
+  needed setting;
+- no robust large-data stability theorem is supplied locally for that setting;
+- and no replacement compactness structure is provided that would justify
+  leaving the inherited suitable-weak / LEI architecture.
+
+So the correct Step-1 ruling is not "weak runner-up." It is
+`not admitted for this chain`.
+
+Filed from:
